	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">jwdonal wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">but the actual schematic when printed to PDF (or whatever) is ultra-high resolution.</div><br />It's not technically correct to call it &quot;ultra-high resolution&quot; because because PDF is not a raster format, so there's no &quot;resolution&quot; to worry about (unless the program prints the schematics as raster images inside the PDF -- not likely). SVG is also a vector format so there's no difference between the two formats when it comes to this.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
