	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Legible SNES Schematics</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There's no particular reason to care about PDF vs SVG: they're both widely supported vector formats. (Some other ones, such as DXF, HPGL, Postscript, EMF, RIPscrip, &amp;c aren't as wide-spread, popular, supported on more than one OS, or even have modern viewers).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


